revision.text:
The '''African Beach Games''' is a continental multi-sport event held among athletes from the Africa. The Games are organised under the governance of the [[Association of National Olympic Committees of Africa]] (ANOCA). The Games were announced by the ANOCA President, '''Lassana Palenfo''', in May 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1027341/palenfo-encouraged-to-run-for-fourth-term-as-anoca-president-as-african-beach-games-receives-green-light|title=Palenfo encouraged to run for fourth term as ANOCA President as African Beach Games receives green light|date=1431759780|access-date=2018-08-08}}</ref>
All of the competing nations are from the [[Africa|African]] continent. The first Games are due to be held on the island of [[Sal, Cape Verde (municipality)|Sal]], Cabo Verde ([[Cape Verde]]) in June 2019. The Games were awarded to the Cabo Verdean Olympic Committee (COC) at the ANOCA General Assembly in Djibouti in May 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.insidethegames.biz/articles/1046957/cape-verde-set-to-be-awarded-african-beach-games-at-anoca-general-assembly|title=Cape Verde set to be awarded African Beach Games at ANOCA General Assembly|date=1486905480|access-date=2018-08-08}}</ref>
The host contract was signed in March 2018 between the City Hall of Sal, the [[Association of National Olympic Committees of Africa]] (ANOCA) and the Cabo Verdean Olympic Committee (COC), to carry out of the first African Beach Games 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.inforpress.publ.cv/sal-city-hall-formalizes-agreement-to-host-the-2019-african-beach-games/?lang=en|title=Sal: City Hall formalizes agreement to host the 2019 African Beach Games - Inforpress|date=2018-03-14|work=Inforpress|access-date=2018-08-08|language=en-US}}</ref>
