{{Infobox person | name = Lennart Green | image = Lennart Green 2006.jpg | image_size = | alt = <!-- see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = Green in March, 2006 | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1941|12|25|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Västervik]], [[Sweden]]<ref>''Swedish Census 1970''.</ref> | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = Swedish | occupation = [[Magic (illusion)|Magician]] | known_for = Magic tricks. Mainly card magic. | notable works = | flourished = | awards = | misc = }}
'''Sven Lennart Green''' (born 25 December 1941) is a Swedish world champion close-up/card [[magic (illusion)|magician]], a title which he won in 1991 at the [[FISM]] convention in [[Lausanne]], Switzerland.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fism.org/web/championship-contests/fism-winners/fism-winners-1991-to-1997/ |title=World Championship of Magic – Winners 1991 to 1997 |publisher=FISM |date= |accessdate=2013-02-24}}</ref> He is known for his seemingly chaotic routines which, in spite of first appearances, display great skill.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elusionist.com/audio/Lennart-Preview.wmv |title=Informal video of Green performing |date= |accessdate=2013-02-24}}</ref> His original techniques and presentation style form an unorthodox and innovative contribution to [[sleight of hand]] magic.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://eprints.hud.ac.uk/19002/ |title=Lennart Green and the Modern Drama of Sleight of Hand |date= |accessdate=2013-10-30}}</ref>
Green began practicing magic at the age of 18<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QyaxK3HXQJ0</ref>. Green competed at the 1988 [[FISM]] convention in [[The Hague]], Netherlands, and was erroneously disqualified because the judges believed he had used [[shill|stooges]] in his act to shuffle the cards.<ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://www.geniimagazine.com/forums/ubbthreads.php?ubb=showflat&Number=210405 |title=Lennert Green Biography (translated and posted here) |publisher=Geniimagazine.com |date=1941-12-25 |accessdate=2013-02-24}}</ref> In 1991, he performed the same act but insisted that the judges themselves shuffle the cards to prove that he used no stooges. The judges then awarded him first place.<ref>[http://93.97.176.48/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=15&Itemid=63&lang=en FISM History Part 6<!-- Bot generated title -->]{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
Green has appeared on the fourth [[The World's Greatest Magic|World's Greatest Magic]] [[television]] special. He lives in [[Gothenburg]], Sweden, and lectures internationally.
He appeared at [[TED (conference)|TED]] in February 2005, where he performed his signature card routine.<ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://www.ted.com/index.php/talks/lennart_green_does_close_up_card_magic.html |title=TED Talks: Lennart Green does close-up card magic |publisher=Ted.com |date= |accessdate=2013-02-24}}</ref>
Privately, Green has worked 7 years as a doctor in Sweden<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QyaxK3HXQJ0</ref>. In 2014 Green suffered a stroke that prevented him from performing lectures in the following months. He has since fully recovered<ref>http://www.m.geniimagazine.com/viewtopic.php?t=44861</ref>.
