{{Infobox Magazine |title = Pambata |image_file = |image_size = |image_caption = |editor = |editor_title = |staff_writer = |frequency = Bimonthly |circulation = |category = [[Magazine]] |company = |publisher = Communication Foundation for Asia |firstdate = 1979 |country = [[Philippines]] |language = [[English language|English]]/[[Filipino language|Filipino]] |website = http://cfamedia.org/ |issn = }} The '''''Pambata''''' is a children's magazine published since 1979 by the Communication Foundation for Asia (CFA) founded by Rev. Cornelio Lagerwey, a [[Dutch people|Dutch]] [[missionary]]. Its office is located in [[Santa Mesa, Manila]], [[Philippines]]. It is an academic supplement in the grade schools for such subjects as [[science]], [[mathematics]], [[English language|English]] and [[social sciences]]. As such, it provides information on science and [[technology]], [[grammar]] and [[vocabulary]], [[history]] and [[geography]], [[health]], mathematics, [[literature]] and the [[art]]s. It received special citations from the Philippine Board on Books for Young People (PBBY) in 1999 and the Catholic Mass Media Awards (CMMA) in 2000. Its sister publications are ''Gospel Komiks'', [[English language|English]] and [[Filipino language|Filipino]] editions, ''Baby Jesus'' for [[preschool|pre-elementary]] and [[kindergarten]] pupils, ''Jesus'' for primary school students, ''Gospel Komiks Magazine'' for [[young people]], and ''Gospel Now'' for [[high school]] and early [[college]] students.<ref>[http://cfamedia.org/main/?page_id=2290 The ''Pambata'' Magazine]</ref>
